","tags":["Coding"]},{"location":"blog/Tutorial/mkdocs/mkdocs-github-actions-build/","title":"如何使用 Github Actions 部署 mkdocs","text":"

正如大家所见,我的博客使用的是 mkdocs + mkdocs-material + Giscus 评论系统的组合. 正当我想从 Marketplace 寻找一个可以部署 mkdocs 的评论系统时,发现全部是为 mkdocs 作为项目文档制作的,部署在 gh-pages 分支上的 Action.

于是我萌生了写一个的想法.

本 Action 可以构建静态网页,commit到github根目录(给netlify用)

(有些小bug)

name: Deploy mkdocs
on:
push:
paths:
- 'mkdocs-src/**'
workflow_dispatch:
jobs:
build:
runs-on: ubuntu-latest
steps:
- name: setup python
uses: actions/setup-python@v4
with:
python-version: '3.10'
- name: install
run: |
pip install mkdocs-material
- name: build static
run: |
git clone 你的仓库地址 
cd 你的用户名.github.io
shopt -s extglob
rm -rf !(README.md|mkdocs-src|.git|.github)
git init
cd mkdocs-src
mkdocs build
cd site
mv -f * ../..
git config --global user.email "你的Github邮箱"
git config --global user.name "你的Github昵称"
git add --all
git commit -m "deploy automatically by github actions"
- name: push
run: |
cd find-nick.github.io
git init
git remote rm origin
git remote add origin https://${{ secrets.MKDOCS_TOKEN }}@你的仓库地址
git push --set-upstream origin main

使用时需注意要在 Github 的 Settings->Developer settings->Personal access tokens->Token(classic) 中申请一个Token,只需要把 repo 勾上即可.

申请Token

然后复制token,到你的用户名.github.io仓库中建立一个新的 Secret(仓库Settings->Security->Actions->New repository secret). (位于https://github.com/你的用户名/你的用户名.github.io/settings/secrets/actions/new)

Name 填 MKDOCS_TOKEN,Secret 填 你刚刚复制的Token.

然后就可以愉快的写博客了:D

"},{"location":"games/2048/#license","title":"License","text":"

"},{"location":"games/2048/#donations","title":"Donations","text":"

I made this in my spare time, and it's hosted on GitHub (which means I don't have any hosting costs), but if you enjoyed the game and feel like buying me coffee, you can donate at my BTC address: 1Ec6onfsQmoP9kkL3zkpB6c5sA4PVcXU2i. Thank you very much!

"},{"location":"games/2048/CONTRIBUTING/","title":"Contributing","text":"

Changes and improvements are more than welcome! Feel free to fork and open a pull request.

Please follow the house rules to have a bigger chance of your contribution being merged.

"},{"location":"games/2048/CONTRIBUTING/#house-rules","title":"House rules","text":""},{"location":"games/2048/CONTRIBUTING/#how-to-make-changes","title":"How to make changes","text":"
  • To make changes, create a new branch based on master (do not create one from gh-pages unless strictly necessary) and make them there, then create a Pull Request to master. gh-pages is different from master in that it contains sharing features, analytics and other things that have no direct bearing with the game. master is the "pure" version of the game.
  • If you want to modify the CSS, please edit the SCSS files present in style/: main.scss and others. Don't edit the main.css, because it's supposed to be generated. In order to compile your SCSS modifications, you need to use the sass gem (install it by running gem install sass once Ruby is installed). To run SASS, simply use the following command: sass --unix-newlines --watch style/main.scss SASS will automatically recompile your css when changed.
  • Rakefile contains some tasks that help during development. Feel free to add useful tasks if needed.
  • Please use 2-space indentation when editing the JavaScript. A .jshintrc file is present, which will help your code to follow the guidelines if you install and run jshint.
  • Please test your modification thoroughly before submitting your Pull Request.
"},{"location":"games/2048/CONTRIBUTING/#changes-that-might-not-be-accepted","title":"Changes that might not be accepted","text":"

We have to be conservative with the core game. This means that some modifications won't be merged, or will have to be evaluated carefully before being merged:

  • Undo/redo features
  • Save/reload features
  • Changes to how the tiles look or their contents
  • Changes to the layout
  • Changes to the grid size
"},{"location":"games/2048/CONTRIBUTING/#changes-that-are-welcome","title":"Changes that are welcome","text":"
  • Bug fixes
  • Compatibility improvements
  • "Under the hood" enhancements
  • Small changes that don't have an impact on the core gameplay
